radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases are clear. The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring 10 mm with moderate mucosal hyperenhancement and surrounding fat stranding/fluid, compatible with acute appendicitis. No appendicolith and no bowel obstruction. Additionally, a 10 mm hypodensity within segment III of the liver likely represents a hemangioma. Otherwise, the liver is unremarkable.
